abstract: The secretary of state met with President Volodymyr Zelensky in Kyiv, during the impeachment trial of President Trump over a pressure campaign against Ukraine.
snippet: The secretary of state met with President Volodymyr Zelensky in Kyiv, during the impeachment trial of President Trump over a pressure campaign against Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Friday that the Trump administration was committed to supporting Ukraine in its defense against aggression by Russia, which invaded and annexed part of the country and is supporting a separatist insurgency.

abstract: An Elle magazine advice columnist who is suing Donald Trump for defamation for denying he raped her approximately 24 years ago wants the U.S. president to provide a DNA sample to see if he came into contact with the dress she said she wore.
snippet: An Elle magazine advice columnist who is suing Donald Trump for defamation for denying he raped her approximately 24 years ago wants the U.S. president to provide a DNA sample to see if he came into contact with the dress she said she wore.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — An Elle magazine advice columnist who is suing Donald Trump for defamation for denying he raped her approximately 24 years ago wants the U.S. president to provide a DNA sample to see if he came into contact with the dress she said she wore.
headline_main: Trump Rape Accuser Seeks DNA Sample From U.S. President
headline_print_headline: Trump Rape Accuser Seeks DNA Sample From U.S. President

abstract: President Donald Trump said on Thursday the United States was working very closely with China on the coronavirus outbreak and he believed it was under control.
snippet: President Donald Trump said on Thursday the United States was working very closely with China on the coronavirus outbreak and he believed it was under control.
lead_paragraph: WARREN, Mich. — President Donald Trump said on Thursday the United States was working very closely with China on the coronavirus outbreak and he believed it was under control.
headline_main: Trump Says Coronavirus Outbreak Is 'Very Well Under Control'
headline_print_headline: Trump Says Coronavirus Outbreak Is 'Very Well Under Control'

abstract: Republican Senator Lamar Alexander said on Thursday that he would vote against calling witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to hear from current and former top Trump aides.
snippet: Republican Senator Lamar Alexander said on Thursday that he would vote against calling witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to hear from current and former top Trump aides.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican Senator Lamar Alexander said on Thursday that he would vote against calling witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to hear from current and former top Trump aides.
headline_main: Key U.S. Senator Alexander Says He Will Not Vote for Impeachment Witnesses

abstract: Britain formally withdrew from the European Union at 11 p.m. on Friday, after nearly half a century of membership.
snippet: Britain formally withdrew from the European Union at 11 p.m. on Friday, after nearly half a century of membership.
lead_paragraph: At 11 p.m. — midnight in Brussels and 6 p.m. in New York — Britain officially left the European Union. Flags lined Parliament Square and the Mall, the ceremonial avenue leading to Buckingham Palace, and government buildings were lit up in the red, white and blue of the Union Jack.

abstract: The U.S. Senate is holding an impeachment trial on charges by the House of Representatives that President Donald Trump abused his powers and obstructed a congressional inquiry into whether he put pressure on Ukraine to investigate Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. Senate is holding an impeachment trial on charges by the House of Representatives that President Donald Trump abused his powers and obstructed a congressional inquiry into whether he put pressure on Ukraine to investigate Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden.
headline_main: Republican Senators to Watch in Battle Over Trump Impeachment Trial Witnesses

abstract: The No. 3 Republican in the U.S. Senate said on Thursday Republicans were prepared to stay through the "completion" of President Donald Trump's impeachment trial whether late on Friday or on Saturday.
snippet: The No. 3 Republican in the U.S. Senate said on Thursday Republicans were prepared to stay through the "completion" of President Donald Trump's impeachment trial whether late on Friday or on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The No. 3 Republican in the U.S. Senate said on Thursday Republicans were prepared to stay through the "completion" of President Donald Trump's impeachment trial whether late on Friday or on Saturday.
headline_main: Senior Republican Sees 'Completion' of Impeachment Trial Friday or Saturday
headline_print_headline: Senior Republican Sees 'Completion' of Impeachment Trial Friday or Saturday

abstract: The head of the U.S. House Judiciary panel said it might be a good idea for the House of Representatives to subpoena President Donald Trump's former national security adviser John Bolton if the Senate does not call him as an impeachment trial witness, CNN reported.
snippet: The head of the U.S. House Judiciary panel said it might be a good idea for the House of Representatives to subpoena President Donald Trump's former national security adviser John Bolton if the Senate does not call him as an impeachment trial witn...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The head of the U.S. House Judiciary panel said it might be a good idea for the House of Representatives to subpoena President Donald Trump's former national security adviser John Bolton if the Senate does not call him as an impeachment trial witness, CNN reported.
headline_main: Nadler Says House Could Subpoena Bolton if Senate Doesn't-CNN
